  Reviewed as a delta against the 1.0.100 proof. 1.0.102 is a pure cleanup
  release: MSRV bumped 1.39 -> 1.68 and edition 2018 -> 2021, all
  `anyhow_no_ptr_addr_of`, `anyhow_no_core_unwind_safe`,
  `anyhow_no_fmt_arguments_as_str`, and `anyhow_no_unsafe_op_in_unsafe_fn_lint`
  cfg branches are deleted, and the optional `backtrace` crate dependency is
  removed. The `backtrace` feature is retained as an empty no-op for
  consumer compat. Net effect on the audit surface: strictly less unsafe
  code, no semantic changes.
  
  Concern #1 (malicious/suspicious): build.rs only got smaller — it no
  longer emits the `std_backtrace`/`anyhow_no_ptr_addr_of`/etc cfgs that
  targeted pre-1.65 rustc. Still only rustc version probing via
  compile_probe writing into OUT_DIR/probe and removing it; no network,
  no shell-out beyond rustc, no writes outside OUT_DIR. Cargo.toml has
  zero runtime deps (only the empty `backtrace`/`std` features and
  dev-deps). License, repo, author unchanged.
  
  Concern #2 (unsafe + SAFETY): The entire `mod capture` in
  src/backtrace.rs is gone — including the `UnsafeCell<Capture>` and
  `unsafe impl Sync for LazilyResolvedCapture` block from the manual
  `backtrace`-crate-based path. backtrace.rs is now 49 lines and uses
  std::backtrace::Backtrace unconditionally when `feature = "std"` is
  on. The dead `object_mut`/`object_downcast_mut`/`context_chain_downcast_mut`
  variants in src/error.rs (gated on the removed `anyhow_no_ptr_addr_of`
  cfg) are deleted. Remaining `unsafe` is the same vtable/thin-pointer
  pattern as 1.0.100: every `unsafe fn` in src/error.rs has a preceding
  `// Safety:` comment naming the invariant ("requires layout of *e to
  match ErrorImpl<E>", "passing vtable that operates on the right type",
  etc.). ensure.rs::Buf and ptr.rs are byte-identical in their unsafe
  shape. `#![deny(unsafe_op_in_unsafe_fn)]` is now unconditional at
  lib.rs:212. Comments use `// Safety:` not the canonical `// SAFETY:`;
  consistent with 1.0.100 — no cap applied.
  
  Concern #3 (miri): .github/workflows/ci.yml miri job is unchanged —
  still runs `cargo miri test` with MIRIFLAGS=-Zmiri-strict-provenance
  (lines 123-135). Vtable / pointer arithmetic stays under miri coverage.
  
  Concern #4 (correctness): No new functional changes; the diff is
  config/cfg removal plus syntactic modernization (`as *const T` ->
  `.cast_const()`, `as *mut E` -> `.cast_mut()`, `match ... { Some => ..,
  None => return }` -> `let Some(...) = ... else { return }`). No new
  bug shapes introduced. The `pub fn Ok` got `#[inline]` added — pure
  optimization.
  
  Rating: positive (inherited from 1.0.100; the changes reduce unsafe
  surface without altering semantics).
