issues:
- id: unsafe-missing-safety-comments
  severity: low
  comment: |
    Three of four `unsafe` blocks lack the conventional `// SAFETY:`
    prefix: src/foreign/core/array.rs:21, src/foreign/core/array.rs:38,
    and src/foreign/core/str.rs:15. The reasoning is sound in each
    case, but the project convention is not followed. Combined with
    the absence of miri in CI, this caps the rating at neutral.
comment: |-
  The `arbitrary` crate provides the `Arbitrary` trait and an `Unstructured`
  byte source for structure-aware fuzzing. It is the canonical crate for
  this purpose in the rust-fuzz ecosystem.
  
  Read every `.rs` file under `src/` (lib.rs, error.rs, size_hint.rs,
  unstructured.rs, and every file under src/foreign/{core,alloc,std}/).
  No build.rs (build = false in Cargo.toml). The only optional dependency
  is `derive_arbitrary` ~1.4.0, which is a separate proc-macro crate not
  bundled here. CI (.github/workflows/rust.yml) runs build, tests, clippy,
  rustfmt, and a 3-minute libFuzzer run of `int_in_range` -- but no miri.
  
  No signs of malicious behaviour: no obfuscation, no network/FS access,
  no env-var harvesting, no `std::process`, no `include_bytes!` blobs, no
  `transmute`, no inline asm.
  
  Four `unsafe` blocks:
    - src/foreign/core/array.rs:21 (Drop): no `// SAFETY:` prefix. The
      reasoning is correct (drops only the initialized prefix tracked by
      ArrayGuard), but the convention is not followed.
    - src/foreign/core/array.rs:38 (try_create_array body): no
      `// SAFETY:` prefix. The unsafe block writes through a raw pointer
      and calls `MaybeUninit::assume_init`; correctness depends on the
      ArrayGuard above and on every callback succeeding before
      `mem::forget(guard)`.
    - src/foreign/core/str.rs:15 (`str::from_utf8_unchecked`): no
      `// SAFETY:` prefix; there is a `debug_assert!(str::from_utf8(...).is_ok())`
      inside the block. The invariant (utf8 valid up to `valid_up_to()`)
      is straightforward but the prefix is missing.
    - src/foreign/alloc/ffi/c_str.rs:11 (`CString::from_vec_unchecked`):
      has a proper `// SAFETY: all zero bytes have been removed` comment.
  
  Per AGENTS.md concern #2, any unsafe block lacking a SAFETY comment
  caps the rating at `neutral`; three of four blocks are missing the
  prefix.
  
  Per concern #3, the unsafe code here is pure-Rust pointer manipulation
  and `from_utf8_unchecked` -- all miri-testable -- but CI does not run
  miri. That alone would cap at `positive`. The combined cap is `neutral`.
  
  Functional correctness (concern #4): no reproducible bugs found.
  Minor cosmetic notes that do not affect rating:
    - src/foreign/core/char.rs:6 doc-comment says "highest unicode code
      point is 0x11_FFFF" -- the actual constant `CHAR_END = 0x11_0000`
      and the modulo are correct, but the comment number is a typo for
      0x10_FFFF.
    - src/size_hint.rs `and` / `and_all` use plain `+`, which would panic
      in debug or wrap in release if a downstream impl returned huge
      bounds. Not reachable from anything in this crate.
