comment: |-
  Reviewed as a delta against 1.5.0. The on-disk diff between 1.5.0 and 1.5.1 is
  test-only: src/ (lib.rs, rustc.rs, version.rs, error.rs, tests.rs) is byte-
  identical, Cargo.toml gains `harness = false` for the `wrappers` test, the
  shell script tests/wrap_ignored is removed, and tests/wrappers.rs is rewritten
  as a harness-free binary that uses `env::current_exe()` as its own "ignored"
  rustc wrapper instead of invoking the deleted shell script. README adds the
  1.5.1 changelog entry confirming this ("Refactor the `test_wrappers` test
  without any shell script").
  
  Concern #1 (supply chain): no new behavior reaches consumers. Tests are not
  published to dependents and no library code, build script, or proc-macro is
  altered. Cargo.toml still has `build = false`, no proc-macro, zero runtime
  deps. License (Apache-2.0 OR MIT), repository, and authorship unchanged.
  
  Concern #2 / #3 (unsafe + miri): the crate contains no `unsafe`; grep across
  src/ returns zero hits. Concerns #2 and #3 don't apply, same as 1.5.0.
  
  Concern #4 (correctness): nothing in the diff changes library semantics.
  The new tests/wrappers.rs has a small main() that dispatches on argv: with no
  args it runs `test_wrappers()` (only on unix); with args it impersonates a
  no-op rustc wrapper, printing a known release string for `--version` and
  draining stdin on `-`. The new `wrap_ignored` step uses `env::current_exe()`
  rather than `./tests/wrap_ignored`; the test binary itself is the wrapper, so
  no shell script is needed. This is purely a test refactor.
  
  Did NOT run any code (no cargo build/test/expand) per project rules. Rating
  inherited from 1.5.0: positive.
